com.percussion.services.assembly
Interface IPSAssemblyResult

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, IPSAssemblyItem, IPSDeliveryItem, Serializable
public interface IPSAssemblyResult
extends IPSAssemblyItem, IPSDeliveryItem

Each assembler creates an assembly result, one or more per content item being assembled. An assembly result is a self contained unit that both contains and describes the result of the assembly process.

For textual assemblers the mime type will normally be text/html or text/xml. Binary assemblers may vary considerably, with typical result types being image/jpeg or application/pdf.

While result data may be internally held in either the file system or memory, it is at the choice of the caller whether to retrieve the contents via IPSDeliveryItem.getResultData() or getResultStream().

Author:
dougrand

getResultStream

InputStream getResultStream()
Get the result data in stream form. This is preferred for large output data to avoid having too much data in memory at any one moment. The result data's format is dependent on the assembler used, and may be either binary or text. The recipient may need to coerce the result to a particular format.

After the returned stream is closed, any underlying data will be cleared. So calling this method should be the last thing done with the assembly results.

Specified by:
getResultStream in interface IPSDeliveryItem
Returns:
the result stream, the contents are entirely dependent on the assembler and may be either text or binary data. If the status is FAILURE then the result stream may be null, but should contain a user readable error message in UTF-8 encoding. The stream must be closed by the caller.

toResultString

String toResultString()
                      throws IllegalStateException,
                             UnsupportedEncodingException
Internally we need to obtain the results as a string for use in slot results. The returned string assumes that the character encoding in the result's mimetype should be used in converting from the result byte array back to a string.

Returns:
a string representation of the result data, never null.
Throws:
IllegalStateException - if this is not a textual result
UnsupportedEncodingException - if the charset isn't supported

isPaginated

boolean isPaginated()
Tells the caller whether this assembly item is paginated. Paginated items are not processed, but rather queried and cloned. The item should define the binding value $sys.pagecount, which will tell the system how many clones to create. The clones will each have the binding $sys.page set to inform the assembly system what page is being assembled.

Returns:
true if this result should be paginated.
